Kaveel Singh, News24The taxi which burst into flames. (Supplied, SAPS) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Port Elizabeth &ndash; Two men were killed when a car and a minibus taxi collided on the N2 near Butterworth on Friday, Eastern Cape police said. A Toyota Quantum travelling from East London crashed into a car coming from Butterworth around noon, Captain Jackson Manatha said.The Quantum burst into flames and a passenger burnt to death. The second victim was a passenger in the car.&nbsp;Police were investigating the cause of the accident.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.